all religious
minorities in every context, I
think, has

26:54.279 --> 27:01.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been certainly a concern for the
pope, and,
you know, for Orthodox
Christians as well.

27:01.420 --> 27:09.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The care for our brothers,
whether they are
Christians or not, should be
something that's

27:09.194 --> 27:10.996 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
foremost in our hearts.

27:11.096 --> 27:16.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, you know, the Orthodox, not
only during
communist times, but in
previous, you know,

27:17.069 --> 27:22.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
decades and centuries, have
often lived in
various contexts of persecution
and strife,

27:22.741 --> 27:30.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but also living together with
Muslims, for
example, in various countries,
where -- the

27:30.249 --> 27:39.024 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
very places where strife
